es.csic.iiia.nsm.agent.language

Class PredicatesDomains

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.csic.iiia.nsm.agent.language.PredicatesDomains

  • public class PredicatesDomains
extends java.lang.Object
    Domains for each possible predicate in the contexts of the agents. Each predicate has a particular domain, which is represented as a taxonomy of terms. The taxonomy represents the generalisation relationships between the terms of a predicate's domain
    Author:
    "Javier Morales (jmorales@iiia.csic.es)"

      • getGeneralisationLevel

        public int getGeneralisationLevel(java.lang.String predicate,
                                  java.lang.String term)
        Returns the level of generalisation of the given term in the taxonomy (i.e., the domain) of the given predicate. The generalisation level indicates the position (i.e., height) of the term in the taxonomy of the predicate's domain. As an example, while a "leaf" term in the taxonomy has level 0, its immediate parent has level 1, and the parent of the parent has level 2
        Parameters:
        predicate - the predicate
        term - the term
        Returns:
        the level of generalisation of the given term in the taxonomy (i.e., the domain) of the given predicate
        See Also:
        Taxonomy

      • isTop

        public boolean isTop(java.lang.String predicate,
                     java.lang.String term)
        Returns true if the given term is in the top of the taxonomy (i.e., the domain) of the given predicate. In other words, it returns true if the term is the most general term in the predicate's domain
        Parameters:
        predicate - the predicate
        term - the term
        Returns:
        true if the given term is in the top of the taxonomy (i.e., the domain) of the given predicate
